The roads are all clear.
I'm gonna head back to my car.

39:58.657 --> 40:00.310
SARAH:Okay.

40:00.354 --> 40:02.574
Do you need me
to give you a ride?

40:02.617 --> 40:04.837
Oh, no thanks.
I'm-I'm good walking.

40:04.880 --> 40:07.361
Nothing like the morning
after a snowfall.

40:07.405 --> 40:10.582
So, uh, so long, you guys.

40:10.625 --> 40:13.019
Weston, it was nice to meet you.

40:13.062 --> 40:16.283
You, too, Paul.
Be careful out there.

40:18.677 --> 40:20.156
♪ Till hurt starts...

40:20.200 --> 40:22.594
Okay, I know technically
we can leave,

40:22.637 --> 40:26.467
but... [sighs]
do we have to?

40:26.511 --> 40:27.468
No...

40:27.512 --> 40:28.861
No?
No.

40:28.904 --> 40:30.166
[groans]

40:30.210 --> 40:33.126
♪ Let it go by, let it go by

40:33.169 --> 40:38.392
♪ Let it go by,
let it go by... ♪

40:39.741 --> 40:43.571
Good news.
The plows are out.

40:43.615 --> 40:45.094
[sighs]

40:45.138 --> 40:46.922
That is good news.

40:46.966 --> 40:48.576
♪ Let it go by...

40:48.620 --> 40:51.405
I'd offer to take Bella home,
but I'm sure I'm the last person

40:51.449 --> 40:54.930
she wants to be around.She already asked me
while you were asleep.

40:54.974 --> 40:58.368
So we're heading out now.Thanks, Groves.

